nd correspondence between publishers and authors. The Latin American examples provide particularly rich information about the processes of institutionalization in the Western world, as well as new perspectives for a contemporary mapping of world literature beyond the established dynamics of canonization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aBuchmärkte. 4aLateinamerikanische Literaturen. 4aRezeptionsstudien. 4aWeltliteraturen. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aBook Markets.  aLatin American Literature.  aReception Studies.  aWorld Literature.0 cEPUBz97831107485290 cprintz978311074837640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110748383zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110748383zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110748383/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA